<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Intentionally minimal.

      displayd/displayctl reach the displays through Apple-signed system
      frameworks (CoreDisplay's IOAVService, DisplayServices) loaded at runtime
      via dlopen. Under the hardened runtime, dlopen of an Apple-signed library
      is permitted without any entitlement, and IOKit I2C access is not gated by
      the sandbox — so this is a Developer ID tool with hardened runtime and no
      entitlements, deliberately not a sandboxed / App Store build.

      Do NOT add com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation here: the
      frameworks we load are Apple-signed and pass validation as-is, and
      disabling it only weakens the runtime.

      When the GUI lands and wants to intercept media keys, CGEventTap needs the
      Accessibility *permission* (granted by the user in System Settings), which
      is a TCC prompt at runtime — not a codesign entitlement — so it does not
      belong in this file either.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
